A. A difference in the cultural landscapes between these two places is the style of architectures. In Jerusalem, we can see grand shrines and churches related to Muslim and Jews style of worship. Whereas in India, the architectures are mostly Buddhist temples. Another significant difference of cultural landscape is the difference in diet of the two places. We might not be able to see pork in the cuisine at the place of Image 1, since Muslims are there and pork is one of their taboos. While we may not see beef in the pilgramage site in imagine 2, since the Hindus do not eat beef. 

B. The diffusion of Islamic belief is an example of relocation diffusion because it is spread by the migration of its believers. Islam originated in the Middle East. However, today, many people around the world are Muslims. This is because of the spread of Islam through trade. Indonesia has the most Muslims population today. In the 12th century, Muslims traders from the Middle East brought goods to Southeast Asia. They brought their religion to Indonesia as they traded. This is considered as relocation diffusion.

C.The global spatial pattern of Hinduism differs from that of universalizing religions such as Buddhism because of the different purpose and ideologies these two religions contain. Hinduism originated in India and is an ethnic religion, which most of the followers are local people in India. They do not actively spread their religion to people all around the world. Whereas a universalizing religion, like Buddhism, followers spread their belief to all around the world. Today, we can see places with people believing in Buddhism outside of Asia where Buddhism first originated. This difference in global spatial pattern is because of the different appeals of the two religions.

D. A cultural effect of the migration pattern of image 2 would be the division of sects of Buddhism. As Buddhism diffuses, it is split into Mahayana Buddhism  and Theravada Buddhism. This is because of the different migration pattern when Buddhism is being spread.



E. Religion could act as a strong centrifugal force to a country because of the diversity of religions. In Israel, specifically Jerusalem, there are many people with different religions, such as Muslims, Christians, and Jews. This could create brutal conflicts since the people have different beliefs. These conflicts may make a nation less unified, and maybe ultimately leads to the separation of states. 




A. From 2001 to 2016, East Asia produces more pounds per acres of wheat than that of Europe. Europe in a higher stage of demographic transition model, which the natural increase rate is declining. There are gradually less workforce being able to work in the farmlands; therefore, the yield of agricultural product decreases. Whereas in Asia, agricultural activities are active. In China, for example, the natural increase rate is relatively high. As a result, more labor could be used for wheat farming, and more yields of wheat is produced.

B. Mechanization and better irrigation made farming more productive in South Asia. India has a large population of 1.2 billion, but in recent years, the country is able to sustain the domestic needs of food by their own agriculture. This is because of the more yield resulted from mechanization and better irrigation system.

C. Green revolution impacted African countries differently to East Asian countries because of the different in climate. Many African countries are dry and arid, making growing food extremely difficult. Whereas in East Asia, there is abundance of water that favors food to grow. As a result, the Green Revolution brought more significant impact to African countries because it brings higher yield seeds. Now, even without favorable climates, African countries could produce more crops than usual because of the new techology (higher yield seeds) brought by the Green Revolution.

D. In Africa, wheat production have been rising. The fertility rate there is also high. Through this, we can see that there is a positive correlation between food yields and fertility rates.
